				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I will be the first to admit. We are a little over-powered. K we are alot overpowered. The slow is a  main factor. Yeah it isn't to super till level 65, but a 65% slow is freaking WOW! I can see that needing some nerfing. There is no problem with anything else really. 
<br />
              The pet proc picks off where a paladins stun spells leave off at 55.  This is why a paladina dna  BL duo works quite effectively. Grant it not as long as pally stun, but helps greatly when taking casters.
<br />
       Paragon is added utility but doesn't add to much that it makes or breaks most raids, and this gets ablied to all classes in raid so it is helping your mana pull too and the healing factor probably will keep you alive when the clerics are too busy keeping the tanks alive. (shut it on paragon)
<br />
       Beasty buffs are a too fold issue. Spiritual light line isn't a bad line and is a nice line to have. It should be taken away, it isn't like we can cast KEI, so don't complain there either. It is nifty regen for both mana and hp. Not a whole over powered device. The other buffs are suito shammy buffs. Though I prefer to buff myself over having Focus, shamans can really do the whole bit a lot better.
<br />
      Pets are what make the beastlord the beastlord. Our pet is no were compared to the mage pet. It has less hp and a little less damage. We also can't summon pets toys on demand. We have to pay a mage for that if we choose. The main damage our pet does is via proc and that is if it isn't reisited.Also have you seen how hard it is to get some of these dang procs, come on!  Our pet heals are pretty long in cast time so not like we are doing the purple club on our pets, e.g. waiting till 10% then healing . It isn't a emergancy button. 
<br />
     Beastlords just got the more defensive and hands on approach to fighting the the mages total offensive outlandish; we nuke better then wizards approach. It is matter of perspective.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=765791" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=765791</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
