			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think if you look at the 3 major pet classes (necro, mage, beastlord), I think all 3 are very powerful in their own respects.  
<br />

<br />
I haven't spoken with my friends about OoW, but pre OoW, necros had free reign on just about anything they wanted to.  If the mob didn't summon, it was dead... if it did summon, there was nothing some good heavy dotting and lifetap tanking couldn't take care of... if stuff hit the fan nothing FD or gate couldn't take care of.  Don't forget their ability to charm very high level undead mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Mages do it well too... if they can get solo pulls, they can take down quite a bit.  Yeah they don't have slow, but they have one hell of tank pet and don't forget they can nuke for days (with malo so they are going to stick pretty well).  And once again... if stuff hits the fan, pet enrages and gate to safety.
<br />

<br />
Beastlords have power... but like the mage, really need solo pulls to handle high end mobs, whereas necros can split.  Without the handy gate/fd spells summoning/overpowering mobs are bad news...  So more risk IMO.  
<br />

<br />
There are plenty of places in OoW and GoD where pets are nothing more than speedbumps...  where no pet class is soloing unless they are kiting.  
<br />

<br />
I think instead of continually nerfing classes (which is driving away lots of people), making it less advantageous to solo is the way to go.  They already started it with increased group exp, who's to say that tweaking those exp bonuses wouldn't cool the masses off about certain classes being able to solo.<br />_________________<br />Grexx
<br />
54 Primalist 
<br />
Maelin Starpyre</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
